---
import { Font } from 'astro:assets';
import ThemeInit from '../../components/ThemeInit.astro';
import ThemeToggle from '../../components/ThemeToggle.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<meta name="robots" content="noindex, nofollow" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		<title>Tile C — The hybrid</title>
		<Font cssVariable="--font-bricolage" preload />
		<Font cssVariable="--font-mono" />
		<ThemeInit />
	</head>
	<body>
		<header class="site">
			<a class="mark" href="/tiles/"><img src="/logo.svg" alt="tp mark — back to tile index" width="36" height="36" /></a>
			<p class="tile-tag" style="view-transition-name: tile-c">Tile C — The hybrid</p>
			<ThemeToggle />
		</header>

		<main>
			<section class="hero">
				<p class="eyebrow">Takis Papadopoulos · Senior product designer · Athens</p>
				<h1 class="display">The medium changes. The&nbsp;job&nbsp;doesn't.</h1>
				<p class="sub">Twenty years of making complex things clear — paper, web, VR, design systems, AI.</p>
			</section>

			<section aria-labelledby="feel-h">
				<h2 id="feel-h">Feel</h2>
				<p class="max-measure">One brand, two temperatures: Home and Lab live in the warm dark room with the cinematic layer; About, Writing and Work are calm, bright and readable. The type has more personality than A's grotesk and more muscle than B's serif — one characterful family doing both jobs. And one experiment: the accent colour keeps Athens time.</p>
				<p class="chips" role="list">
					<span class="chip" role="listitem">warm</span>
					<span class="chip" role="listitem">playful</span>
					<span class="chip" role="listitem">experimental</span>
					<span class="chip" role="listitem">honest</span>
					<span class="chip" role="listitem">typographic</span>
				</p>
			</section>

			<section aria-labelledby="temp-h">
				<h2 id="temp-h">Two temperatures, one site</h2>
				<div class="temp-strip">
					<div class="temp-panel temp-dark">
						<p class="t-caption">Home · Lab</p>
						<p class="temp-title">Always the dark room</p>
						<p class="t-small-ondark">Cinematic layer lives here: reveals, shaders, the hero moment. Fixed dark-warm regardless of theme.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="temp-panel temp-calm">
						<p class="t-caption">About · Writing · Work</p>
						<p class="temp-title">Calm content surfaces</p>
						<p class="t-small">Follow your theme (system default, toggle above), stay quiet, read beautifully. Nothing moves that doesn't have to.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section aria-labelledby="type-h">
				<h2 id="type-h">Type</h2>
				<p class="spec-note">Stand-in face: <strong>Bricolage Grotesque</strong> variable (Mathieu Triay, SIL OFL) — optical size + width + weight axes; grotesk bones, humanist quirks. One family, display to caption.</p>
				<div class="specimen">
					<p class="spec display">Display / clamp(2.75–7rem)</p>
					<p class="spec t-h1">Heading 1 / clamp(2.1–3.5rem)</p>
					<p class="spec t-h2">Heading 2 / clamp(1.65–2.35rem)</p>
					<p class="spec t-h3">Heading 3 / clamp(1.3–1.65rem)</p>
					<p class="spec t-h4">Heading 4 / clamp(1.08–1.25rem)</p>
					<p class="spec t-body">Body / clamp(1–1.125rem) — measure capped at 65ch, line-height 1.6, real quotes “like so”, en-dashes – and tabular numerals 0123456789 where they line up.</p>
					<p class="spec t-small">Small / 0.875rem — metadata and dates.</p>
					<p class="spec t-caption">Caption / 0.8125rem — the fine print with manners.</p>
					<p class="spec t-mono">Mono / JetBrains Mono VF — code, tokens, lab notes.</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section aria-labelledby="colour-h">
				<h2 id="colour-h">Colour — and the living accent</h2>
				<p class="max-measure">Warm neutrals, no pure black or white, tokens in OKLCH with hex fallbacks via <code>light-dark()</code>. The accent is the experiment: it follows the sky over Athens — dawn rose, day blue, dusk amber, night violet. Deterministic, local, zero requests, zero permissions: just the clock, because that's where the site lives. Without JavaScript it rests at dusk amber. Every phase passes AA in both themes.</p>
				<div class="sky-row" id="sky-row">
					<button type="button" class="sky" data-sky-btn="dawn"><span class="dot dot-dawn"></span>dawn<br /><span class="t-caption">05–09</span></button>
					<button type="button" class="sky" data-sky-btn="day"><span class="dot dot-day"></span>day<br /><span class="t-caption">09–18</span></button>
					<button type="button" class="sky" data-sky-btn="dusk"><span class="dot dot-dusk"></span>dusk<br /><span class="t-caption">18–21</span></button>
					<button type="button" class="sky" data-sky-btn="night"><span class="dot dot-night"></span>night<br /><span class="t-caption">21–05</span></button>
				</div>
				<p class="t-caption" id="sky-note">Right now the page rests at dusk (the no-JS default). Buttons preview a phase; the live site would follow the clock.</p>
				<div class="swatches">
					<div class="swatch sw-bg"><span>--bg</span></div>
					<div class="swatch sw-raised"><span>--bg-raised</span></div>
					<div class="swatch sw-text"><span>--text</span></div>
					<div class="swatch sw-muted"><span>--text-muted</span></div>
					<div class="swatch sw-accent"><span>--accent (now)</span></div>
					<div class="swatch sw-border"><span>--border</span></div>
				</div>
				<table>
					<caption>Measured accent contrast per phase (WCAG 2.2) — table sample</caption>
					<thead>
						<tr><th scope="col">Phase</th><th scope="col">On light bg</th><th scope="col">On dark bg</th><th scope="col">Floor</th></tr>
					</thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr><td>dawn</td><td>5.44:1</td><td>8.17:1</td><td>4.5:1</td></tr>
						<tr><td>day</td><td>6.22:1</td><td>8.23:1</td><td>4.5:1</td></tr>
						<tr><td>dusk</td><td>5.48:1</td><td>8.32:1</td><td>4.5:1</td></tr>
						<tr><td>night</td><td>6.39:1</td><td>7.49:1</td><td>4.5:1</td></tr>
						<tr><td>text / bg</td><td>15.98:1</td><td>15.32:1</td><td>4.5:1</td></tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>
			</section>

			<section aria-labelledby="space-h">
				<h2 id="space-h">Space &amp; layout</h2>
				<p class="max-measure">Same scale as the other directions; soft 8px corners and raised surfaces with hairlines — friendlier than A, warmer than B.</p>
				<div class="space-bars">
					<div style="inline-size: var(--space-1)"><span>1 · 0.25rem</span></div>
					<div style="inline-size: var(--space-2)"><span>2 · 0.5rem</span></div>
					<div style="inline-size: var(--space-3)"><span>3 · 1rem</span></div>
					<div style="inline-size: var(--space-4)"><span>4 · 1.5rem</span></div>
					<div style="inline-size: var(--space-5)"><span>5 · 2.5rem</span></div>
					<div style="inline-size: var(--space-6)"><span>6 · 4rem</span></div>
					<div style="inline-size: var(--space-7)"><span>7 · 6.5rem</span></div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section aria-labelledby="comp-h">
				<h2 id="comp-h">Components</h2>

				<p class="max-measure t-body">
					I've designed food-delivery flows, VR tours of ancient stadiums, enterprise design systems and a gaming social network. The thesis project lost its domain and the VR startup never found funding — both taught me more than the wins that followed. These days I split my time between product work and <a href="/tiles/">Zeus</a>, the local-AI studio humming under my desk.
				</p>

				<div class="btn-row">
					<a class="btn btn-primary" href="/tiles/">Read the case study</a>
					<a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/tiles/">Download CV</a>
					<a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/tiles/">All experiments</a>
				</div>

				<div class="card-row">
					<article class="card">
						<p class="chip">design systems</p>
						<h3 class="t-h3">BETA CAE — one system, three realities</h3>
						<p class="t-small">Five years building a design system that spans desktop, web and VR/AR for an engineering suite — one language across every screen and headset.</p>
						<a href="/tiles/">Read the case study</a>
					</article>
					<article class="card">
						<p class="chip chip-live">live</p>
						<h3 class="t-h3">Zeus — the local AI studio</h3>
						<p class="t-small">Agents, voice, image generation — running on one stubborn GPU in Athens. Self-funded; self-inflicted.</p>
						<a href="/tiles/">See the experiments</a>
					</article>
				</div>

				<aside class="callout">
					<p class="t-small"><strong>Token discipline.</strong> Every visual decision on this page is a custom property — including the sky. Change it once, it changes everywhere; the real site keeps this contract in <code>design.md</code>.</p>
				</aside>

				<figure>
					<pre class="code"><code>// the whole living-accent mechanism — runs once, no requests
const h = Number(new Intl.DateTimeFormat('en', &#123;
  hour: 'numeric', hour12: false, timeZone: 'Europe/Athens',
&#125;).format(new Date()));
document.documentElement.dataset.sky =
  h &lt; 5 ? 'night' : h &lt; 9 ? 'dawn' : h &lt; 18 ? 'day' : h &lt; 21 ? 'dusk' : 'night';</code></pre>
					<figcaption class="t-caption">Figure + caption sample. Real code — it sets this page's accent.</figcaption>
				</figure>
			</section>

			<section aria-labelledby="motion-h">
				<h2 id="motion-h">Motion</h2>
				<ul class="max-measure">
					<li><code>--motion-quick: 120ms</code> hovers/presses · <code>--motion-base: 240ms</code> reveals and theme changes.</li>
					<li><strong>Signature:</strong> cross-document View Transition — <a href="/tiles/">back to the index</a>, the title morphs. One pattern, site-wide.</li>
					<li><strong>Split register:</strong> choreography (as on tile A) exists only on the dark surfaces — Home and Lab. Content pages get micro-interactions and nothing else.</li>
					<li><strong>Reduced motion:</strong> the clean core, always readable, nothing moves.</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section aria-labelledby="nf-h">
				<h2 id="nf-h">404 sample</h2>
				<div class="frame-404">
					<p class="display nf-code">404</p>
					<p class="t-h3">Even the Athens sky can't find this page.</p>
					<p class="t-small">It's <span id="phase-word">dusk</span> over there right now; this page is nowhere at all. Let's go somewhere that exists.</p>
					<a class="btn btn-primary" href="/tiles/">Head home</a>
				</div>
			</section>

			<footer class="colophon">
				<p class="t-caption">Stand-in fonts: Bricolage Grotesque (Mathieu Triay) + JetBrains Mono — both SIL OFL, self-hosted woff2, subsetting allowed. Premium upgrade candidate for this direction: <strong>ABC Diatype / Diatype Variable</strong> (Dinamo — perpetual one-off licence priced by company size, quote via licensing@abcdinamo.com; free trial fonts available, including Greek script). Subsetting rights checked before purchase. Buying is a takis decision after the tile pick.</p>
				<p class="t-caption">Theme: system default + manual override. Colours: OKLCH via <code>light-dark()</code>, hex fallback = light set. Accent follows Europe/Athens local time; no JS = dusk. Style tile — deleted after Phase 1 pick.</p>
			</footer>
		</main>

		<script is:inline>
			// living accent: set phase from Athens local time; buttons preview
			(() => {
				const root = document.documentElement;
				const phase = () => {
					const h = Number(new Intl.DateTimeFormat('en', { hour: 'numeric', hour12: false, timeZone: 'Europe/Athens' }).format(new Date()));
					return h < 5 ? 'night' : h < 9 ? 'dawn' : h < 18 ? 'day' : h < 21 ? 'dusk' : 'night';
				};
				const now = phase();
				const apply = (p, label) => {
					root.dataset.sky = p;
					const w = document.getElementById('phase-word');
					if (w) w.textContent = now;
					const note = document.getElementById('sky-note');
					if (note) note.textContent = label;
					document.querySelectorAll('[data-sky-btn]').forEach((b) => {
						b.setAttribute('aria-pressed', String(b.dataset.skyBtn === p));
					});
				};
				apply(now, `Right now it's ${now} in Athens, so the accent is ${now}'s. Buttons preview another phase; the live site would follow the clock.`);
				document.querySelectorAll('[data-sky-btn]').forEach((b) => {
					b.addEventListener('click', () => {
						const p = b.dataset.skyBtn;
						apply(p, p === now ? `Back to real time — it's ${now} in Athens.` : `Previewing ${p}. Real time in Athens says ${now}.`);
					});
				});
			})();
		</script>
	</body>
</html>

<style is:global>
	:root { color-scheme: light dark; }
	:root[data-theme='light'] { color-scheme: light; }
	:root[data-theme='dark'] { color-scheme: dark; }
	@view-transition { navigation: auto; }

	:root {
		/* ---- Tile C tokens. Hex fallback = light; capable browsers get OKLCH light-dark() ---- */
		--bg: #fbf6ef;
		--bg: light-dark(oklch(97.5% 0.011 76.6), oklch(19.6% 0.01 52.9));
		--bg-raised: #f4eee4;
		--bg-raised: light-dark(oklch(95.1% 0.015 80.7), oklch(23.7% 0.016 62.6));
		--text: #211a14;
		--text: light-dark(oklch(22.4% 0.016 62.5), oklch(94% 0.013 71.3));
		--text-muted: #6b5f53;
		--text-muted: light-dark(oklch(49.3% 0.024 67.2), oklch(69.6% 0.023 69.7));
		--border: #e0d6c8;
		--border: light-dark(oklch(88% 0.022 76.5), oklch(33.2% 0.019 63.8));
		--accent-contrast: #fbf6ef;
		--accent-contrast: light-dark(oklch(97.5% 0.011 76.6), oklch(19.6% 0.01 52.9));

		/* living accent — dusk is the resting (no-JS) phase */
		--accent: #8a5a1f;
		--accent: light-dark(oklch(50.9% 0.096 67.6), oklch(76.1% 0.131 67.6));
		--focus-ring: var(--accent);

		--size-display: clamp(2.75rem, 1.1rem + 8vw, 7rem);
		--size-h1: clamp(2.1rem, 1.4rem + 2.8vw, 3.5rem);
		--size-h2: clamp(1.65rem, 1.3rem + 1.4vw, 2.35rem);
		--size-h3: clamp(1.3rem, 1.15rem + 0.7vw, 1.65rem);
		--size-h4: clamp(1.08rem, 1rem + 0.35vw, 1.25rem);
		--size-body: clamp(1rem, 0.96rem + 0.2vw, 1.125rem);
		--size-small: 0.875rem;
		--size-caption: 0.8125rem;

		--space-1: 0.25rem; --space-2: 0.5rem; --space-3: 1rem; --space-4: 1.5rem;
		--space-5: 2.5rem; --space-6: 4rem; --space-7: 6.5rem;

		--motion-quick: 120ms;
		--motion-base: 240ms;
		--ease-out: cubic-bezier(0.2, 0.7, 0.2, 1);

		--radius: 8px;

		/* phase palettes (light-darkened / dark-brightened, all AA — see table) */
		--sky-dawn: #a34a35;
		--sky-dawn: light-dark(oklch(51.9% 0.123 34.6), oklch(75.8% 0.089 34));
		--sky-day: #22608f;
		--sky-day: light-dark(oklch(47.3% 0.099 245.2), oklch(74.8% 0.08 241.7));
		--sky-dusk: #8a5a1f;
		--sky-dusk: light-dark(oklch(50.9% 0.096 67.6), oklch(76.1% 0.131 67.6));
		--sky-night: #5f4ba8;
		--sky-night: light-dark(oklch(48.2% 0.143 289.8), oklch(73.3% 0.111 293.6));
	}
	:root[data-sky='dawn'] { --accent: var(--sky-dawn); }
	:root[data-sky='day'] { --accent: var(--sky-day); }
	:root[data-sky='dusk'] { --accent: var(--sky-dusk); }
	:root[data-sky='night'] { --accent: var(--sky-night); }

	* { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; }
	body {
		background: var(--bg);
		color: var(--text);
		font-family: var(--font-bricolage), system-ui, sans-serif;
		font-size: var(--size-body);
		line-height: 1.6;
		padding: clamp(1rem, 4vw, 3rem);
		max-width: 68rem;
		margin-inline: auto;
	}
	:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--focus-ring); outline-offset: 3px; border-radius: 4px; }
	a { color: var(--accent); text-underline-offset: 0.2em; transition: opacity var(--motion-quick) var(--ease-out), color var(--motion-base) var(--ease-out); }
	a:hover { opacity: 0.8; }

	.site { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: var(--space-3); margin-bottom: var(--space-6); }
	.tile-tag { font-size: var(--size-small); color: var(--text-muted); letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; }
	#theme-toggle {
		font: inherit; font-size: var(--size-caption); cursor: pointer; padding: 0.4rem 0.9rem;
		border-radius: 999px; border: 1px solid var(--border); background: var(--bg-raised); color: var(--text);
	}

	main > section { margin-bottom: var(--space-7); }
	h2 { font-size: var(--size-h2); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
	.max-measure { max-width: 65ch; }

	.hero { padding-block: var(--space-6); }
	.eyebrow { font-size: var(--size-small); color: var(--text-muted); letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
	.display { font-size: var(--size-display); font-weight: 780; line-height: 1; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
	.sub { font-size: var(--size-h4); color: var(--text-muted); max-width: 46ch; }

	/* temperature strip */
	.temp-strip { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(17rem, 1fr)); gap: var(--space-4); }
	.temp-panel { border-radius: var(--radius); padding: var(--space-5) var(--space-4); display: grid; gap: var(--space-2); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
	.temp-title { font-size: var(--size-h3); font-weight: 700; }
	.temp-dark {
		/* fixed dark-warm, theme-independent by design */
		background: #191411;
		background: oklch(19.6% 0.01 52.9);
		color: #f1eae2;
		color: oklch(94% 0.013 71.3);
		border-color: #3d342c;
		border-color: oklch(33.2% 0.019 63.8);
	}
	.temp-dark .t-caption { color: #a79b8e; color: oklch(69.6% 0.023 69.7); }
	.t-small-ondark { font-size: var(--size-small); color: #a79b8e; color: oklch(69.6% 0.023 69.7); }
	.temp-calm { background: var(--bg-raised); }

	/* living accent */
	.sky-row { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--space-3); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
	.sky {
		font: inherit; font-size: var(--size-small); color: var(--text); cursor: pointer;
		background: var(--bg-raised); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius);
		padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4); text-align: center; line-height: 1.5;
	}
	.sky[aria-pressed='true'] { border-color: var(--accent); outline: 1px solid var(--accent); }
	.dot { display: block; inline-size: 1.4rem; block-size: 1.4rem; border-radius: 999px; margin: 0 auto var(--space-2); }
	.dot-dawn { background: var(--sky-dawn); }
	.dot-day { background: var(--sky-day); }
	.dot-dusk { background: var(--sky-dusk); }
	.dot-night { background: var(--sky-night); }
	#sky-note { margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }

	.spec-note { color: var(--text-muted); max-width: 65ch; margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
	.specimen { display: grid; gap: var(--space-3); border-block: 1px solid var(--border); padding-block: var(--space-4); }
	.spec.display { margin: 0; }
	.t-h1 { font-size: var(--size-h1); font-weight: 760; letter-spacing: -0.015em; line-height: 1.05; }
	.t-h2 { font-size: var(--size-h2); font-weight: 700; }
	.t-h3 { font-size: var(--size-h3); font-weight: 680; }
	.t-h4 { font-size: var(--size-h4); font-weight: 640; }
	.t-body { font-size: var(--size-body); max-width: 65ch; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
	.t-small { font-size: var(--size-small); color: var(--text-muted); }
	.t-caption { font-size: var(--size-caption); color: var(--text-muted); }
	.t-mono { font-family: var(--font-mono), monospace; font-size: var(--size-small); }

	.swatches { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(9rem, 1fr)); gap: var(--space-2); margin-block: var(--space-4); }
	.swatch { border-radius: var(--radius); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-3); font-family: var(--font-mono), monospace; font-size: var(--size-caption); }
	.sw-bg { background: var(--bg); }
	.sw-raised { background: var(--bg-raised); }
	.sw-text { background: var(--text); color: var(--bg); }
	.sw-muted { background: var(--text-muted); color: var(--bg); }
	.sw-accent { background: var(--accent); color: var(--accent-contrast); transition: background var(--motion-base) var(--ease-out); }
	.sw-border { background: var(--border); }
	table { border-collapse: collapse; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; font-size: var(--size-small); }
	caption { text-align: left; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: var(--size-caption); margin-bottom: var(--space-2); }
	th, td { text-align: left; padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-4) var(--space-2) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }

	.space-bars { display: grid; gap: var(--space-2); margin-top: var(--space-4); }
	.space-bars div { background: var(--accent); block-size: 1.1rem; border-radius: 3px; position: relative; min-inline-size: 2px; transition: background var(--motion-base) var(--ease-out); }
	.space-bars span { position: absolute; inset-inline-start: calc(100% + 0.75rem); top: 50%; translate: 0 -50%; font-family: var(--font-mono), monospace; font-size: var(--size-caption); color: var(--text-muted); white-space: nowrap; }

	.chips { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--space-2); margin-top: var(--space-3); }
